simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: This function is called at when the Reset command is received. It resets all metrics, which include the Dropped Message Counts, and Queued Message Counts.

parameterdescription.para: A TO_ChannelData_t pointer that references the channel data structure

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: This function is called at when the application is about to load a new configuration table. This will flush the queues and deallocate the messages contained in the queues.

parameterdescription.para: A TO_ChannelData_t pointer that references the channel data structure

simplesect.para: 0 if successful. OSAL error if unsuccessful.

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: This function is called when a ground command is received to query a message flow. An event is raised with the following text format: "PQI=<PQueueIndex> CI=<ChannelID> S=<State> ML=<MsgLimit> QT=<QueueType> D=<DroppedMsgCnt> Q=<QueuedMsgCnt> CQ=<CurrentlyQueuedCnt> HWM=<HighwaterMark>"
TRUE if priority queue is found. FALSE if not found.

briefdescription.para: Checks whether a priority index is valid or not.

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: This function is used internally to determine if an index is to a valid priority queue.

parameterdescription.para: A TO_ChannelData_t pointer that references the channel data structure

simplesect.para: TRUE if priority queue is valid. FALSE if not.
